# Production builds only: set to "full" for the complete website (all pages, signup, etc.).
# Leave unset for instalatori-only (main site). Local `npm run dev` is always full site.
# VITE_SITE_MODE=full

# Optional: API base URL (production/staging). Dev uses proxy /api or localhost.
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-api.vercel.app

# Google Sign-In (GIS/FedCM). Must match GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID configured on the API.
#
# Vercel: Settings → Environment Variables → add VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID for Production
# and Preview (and Development if you use `vercel dev`). Redeploy after saving — Vite
# inlines these at build time; without them the login page shows “lipsește în frontend”.
# Add your Vercel URL(s) to Google Cloud → OAuth client → Authorized JavaScript origins.
#
# Local dev: In Google Cloud Console → Credentials → your OAuth 2.0 Web client →
# “Authorized JavaScript origins”, add BOTH (exact URL, no trailing slash):
#   http://localhost:5173
#   http://127.0.0.1:5173
# Otherwise GIS shows: unregistered_origin. If Vite prints another port (e.g. 5174), add that
# origin too. If you open dev via LAN (http://192.168.x.x:5173), add that exact origin too, or
# use http://localhost:5173. FedCM is off in `vite` dev and on localhost/private IPs so GIS uses
# the classic prompt locally (matches production behavior on Vercel).
VITE_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID=138491232272-dnrcb5thtn8d8cq484vqf4pl5tkva5i2.apps.googleusercontent.com
